Configure Backup Vault

0. Configure Oraganizations to create policies

	a. click on your account name
	b. click on organization
	c. enable aws backup

1. Type : Key Management Service in the aws console search bar and select the first option

2. Click Create Key Button

3. Select Symetric

	a. add tags
	b. descriptions
	c. etc..

4. Create backup vault

	a. backup vaults -> create backup vault
	b. add the kms key
	c. add Name field

5. Create Backup plan

	a. Build new plan
	b. Enter new plan name
	c. Enter the backup vault
	c. Enter backup frequency

6. Assign resources

	a. go to backupplans
	b. select the plan
	c. scroll down to assign  resources

7. wait until tommorow to see the backups in protected assests

	a. only AMI should be visible
	b. No snapshot only in EC2 console
